```csharp
using System;
using System.IO;
using ClamScan;

class Program
{
    static void Main(string[] args)
    {
        // Initialize the ClamAV scanner
        var clam = new ClamScan();

        // Set the path to the ClamAV virus definition database
        clam.SetDatabasePath(@"C:\ProgramData\.clamwin\db");

        // Set the maximum file size that can be scanned (in bytes)
        clam.SetMaxFileSize(10485760); // 10 MB

        // Set the action to take when a virus is detected
        clam.SetVirusScannerAction(VirusScannerAction.Delete);

        // Specify the file to scan
        string filePath = @"C:\Users\user\Downloads\file.exe";

        // Open the file as a stream
        using (FileStream stream = new FileStream(filePath, FileMode.Open, FileAccess.Read))
        {
            // Scan the file for viruses
            ScanResult result = clam.ScanFile(stream);

            // Check if a virus was detected
            if (result.IsVirusDetected)
            {
                Console.WriteLine("Virus detected: {0}", result.VirusName);
            }
            else
            {
                Console.WriteLine("File is clean");
            }
        }
    }
}
```
This program first initializes a new `ClamScan` object, which is the C# wrapper for the ClamAV antivirus engine. It then sets the path to the virus definition database and the maximum file size that can be scanned. It also specifies that the action to take when a virus is detected is to delete the infected file.

Next, it specifies the file to scan and opens it as a stream. The `ScanFile` method is then called to scan the file for viruses. If a virus is detected, the `IsVirusDetected` property of the `ScanResult` object will be `true` and the name of the virus will be stored in the `VirusName` property. Otherwise, the program prints a message indicating that the file is clean.

Note that you will need to have ClamAV installed on your system in order to use this program. You can download ClamAV from the official website (<https://www.clamav.net/downloads>). Additionally, you will need to add a reference to the `ClamScan` library in your project. You can do this by right-clicking on your project in Visual Studio and selecting "Add Reference". Then, navigate to the location where you extracted the ClamScan library and select the ClamScan.dll file.

