Great! Here's some sample code for a code sample block component that meets your requirements. This component uses React for rendering the UI, and the `clipboard.js` library for copying the code to clipboard. You can modify the styling and other aspects of the component to suit your needs.
```javascript
import React, { useState, useEffect } from 'react';
import ClipboardJS from 'clipboard';

const CodeSampleBlock = ({ title, language, code }) => {
  const [copied, setCopied] = useState(false);

  useEffect(() => {
    const clipboard = new ClipboardJS('.copy-btn');

    clipboard.on('success', () => {
      setCopied(true);
      setTimeout(() => {
        setCopied(false);
      }, 2000);
    });

    return () => {
      clipboard.destroy();
    };
  }, []);

  return (
    <div className="code-sample-block">
      <div className="header">
        <div className="title">{title}</div>
        <div className="language">{language}</div>
        <button className="copy-btn" data-clipboard-text={code}>
          {copied ? 'Copied!' : 'Copy'}
        </button>
      </div>
      <div className="body">
        <div className="code-lines">
          {code.split('\n').map((line, index) => (
            <div key={index} className="line-number">{index + 1}</div>
          ))}
        </div>
        <pre className={`code language-${language}`}>
          <code>{code}</code>
        </pre>
      </div>
    </div>
  );
};

export default CodeSampleBlock;
```
To use this component, you can pass the following props:

* `title`: The title of the code sample block
* `language`: The language of the code sample (e.g. "curl", "node.js", etc.)
* `code`: The example code to be displayed in the code sample block.

Here's an example of how to use the component in a React app:
```javascript
import CodeSampleBlock from './CodeSampleBlock';

const Example = () => {
  const curlCode = `curl https://api.example.com -H "Authorization: Bearer <token>"`;

  return (
    <div>
      <CodeSampleBlock title="Example API Request" language="curl" code={curlCode} />
    </div>
  );
};
```
This will render a code sample block component that displays the curl code, with a header section that shows the title, language, and copy button.

